Child Poverty by Household Type:
Children in single parent households are defined as the
biological, adopted, or step children of household
heads in family households where no spouse is present.&nbsp;Other households are those for whom the child's relationship to householder is defined as other relative, foster or unrelated child.&nbsp;Due to small sample sizes in smaller geographies, data are presented in 3-year averages; 2019 = 2017-2019 3-year average.&nbsp;
